(998, 258, 'feature_image_caption', 'Consumer brands and retailers have clear regulations governing unethical supply chain practices within their own organizations.¬† Should an allegation of corrupt practices about an associate be substantiated, an established set of procedures are followed usually leading to termination or even prosecution. ¬†However, very few organizations have equivalent procedures for managing cases of bribery involving external partners.¬† This is a major blind spot.¬† '),
